docs.abstract: With the transfer of a prisoner to Saudi Arabia, the president has now presided over a decrease in the number of detainees he inherited.
docs.snippet: With the transfer of a prisoner to Saudi Arabia, the president has now presided over a decrease in the number of detainees he inherited.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon has transferred a Guantánamo Bay prisoner to the custody of Saudi Arabia, a spokeswoman announced on Wednesday. The handoff is the first time a detainee has left the wartime prison under President Trump, who vowed to fill it back up but has now instead overseen a reduction in its population.

headline.main: U.S. Transfers First Guantánamo Detainee Under Trump, Who Vowed to Fill It
headline.print_headline: Despite Trump’s Vow to Fill Prison, Guantánamo Population Drops

docs.abstract: Minutes before a committee vote, Senator Rand Paul, Republican of Kentucky, bowed to pressure and backed the confirmation of Mike Pompeo to be secretary of state.
docs.snippet: Minutes before a committee vote, Senator Rand Paul, Republican of Kentucky, bowed to pressure and backed the confirmation of Mike Pompeo to be secretary of state.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate Foreign Relations Committee, in a late pivot on Monday evening, approved the confirmation of Mike Pompeo to be the next secretary of state, after Senator Rand Paul, Republican of Kentucky, bowed to pressure from President Trump and dropped his opposition.

headline.main: After Late Vote Switch, Senate Panel Approves Pompeo for Secretary of State
headline.print_headline: Paul Relents, And Pompeo Is Approved By Panel
